item.title: Owner rank help
item.dc:creator: @Bl3nd Bl3nd
item.description:
@Bl3nd wrote:

You do not need to do anything with your character file…You need to go into RegularPlayer.java and put in the code that makes the player rights go to you’re name, which is “mod jd”…

if (cmd[0].equals("admin")) { if (player.getDisplayName().equals("NAME GOES HERE")) { player.setRights(2); } return true; }
then to make it work, you need to enter ::admin, and I believe a mod command is already in the files.

@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“Fox2007, post:16, topic:481766”]To make yourself owner, add this command into RegularPlayer.java

if (cmd[0].equals("admin")) { if (player.getDisplayName().equals("NAME GOES HERE")) { player.setRights(2); } return true; }

Also if you lag, you might need a new graphics card or better ram/processor. Try turning the graphics settings down some. Also, if you cant run or compile, make sure that the JDK version in the run.bat is correct. Try changing the jdk1.7.0_10 to whatever java version you have and make sure you have the directory correct of where your Java is.[/quote]
